The Minister of Water Resources Engr. Adamu Suleiman, has urged for the support of Adamawa Emirate Council in its war against open defecation. Suleiman during courtesy visit on the Lamido, Alhaji Muhammadu Barkindo Mustpaha, said concerted effort of traditional institution is needed to mitigate increasing open deification which the country globally rated high. He encouraged people embrace use of toilets, personal hygiene as open deification could  led to environmental pollution, water borne  diseases, malnutrition  in children. In his remarks, the Lamido reiterated the commitment of the emirate to support the crusade, which he said is tailored at improving personal hygiene of the people. The minister lauded the management of Upper Benue River Basin Development Authority (UBRBDA), Yola for sustaining Kiri Dam, established 40 years in the state. Kiri dam has the capacity of producing hydro power source and irrigation to the people of the state. He said the ministry is planning a separate study on the River Niger and Benue’s master plan for protection against flooding and reclaiming of encroached land. Earlier, Engr Abubakar Muazu, Managing Director, UBRBDA identified coast of diesels to the cultivation of less than 500 hectares of land in Gerio irrigation field. Muazu further lamented the yearly perennial flood, where equipment are evacuated to and from the central store, as some of the challenges bedeviling the irrigation project. 